FBIS4-11346 "drlat080_h_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-080 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 Honduras Texaco Raises Fuel Prices Twice in Less Than 12 Hours Texaco Raises Fuel Prices Twice in Less Than 12 Hours PA2304173294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0341 GMT 23 Apr 94 PA2304173294 Mexico City NOTIMEX Spanish BFN [Text] Tegucigalpa, 22 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- Fuel prices in Honduras changed twice in less than 12 hours, official sources have reported. Texaco changed its prices on the morning of 22 April, but in the afternoon it incorporated the changes that had been decided by the three other fuel distributors. Texaco had set the price of premium gasoline at 10.19 lempiras ($1.40), regular gasoline at 9.57 lempiras ($1.31), and diesel fuel at 7.27 lempiras ($1) a gallon. Nevertheless, the local enterprise DIPPSA [Petroleum Products Distributor Corporation] and the multinational companies Esso and Shell decided to change their prices effective Saturday. The new price structure per gallon (3.785 liters) is as follows: ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Seller |Fuel Type |Prior Price |New Price |New Price in | | | | | |dollars | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Texaco |Premium (in t-|10.19 |10.26 |1.41 | | |he morning) | | | | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Regular (in t-|9.57 |9.64 |1.32 | | |he morning) | | | | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Diesel (in th-|7.27 |7.34 |1.00 | | |e morning) | | | | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Esso |Premium |10.10 |10.38 |1.42 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Regular |9.49 |9.77 |1.34 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Diesel |7.19 |7.44 |1.02 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |DIPPSA |Premium |10.10 |10.40 |1.43 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Regular |9.49 |9.77 |1.34 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Diesel |7.19 |7.47 |1.02 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Shell |Premium |10.10 |10.46 |1.43 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Regular |9.49 |9.84 |1.35 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |Diesel |7.19 |7.54 |1.03 | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- Economy Ministry authorities have said that starting 23 April, people will have to "learn" to live with these kinds of changes, which will be determined by supply and demand.
